statistics.description: The number of times a player who passes the ball to a teammate in a way that leads to a score by field goal, meaning that he or she was "assisting" in the basket. There is some judgment involved in deciding whether a passer should be credited with an assist.

statistics.name: turnovers

statistics.name: assistTurnoverRatio
statistics.description: The average number of assists a player or team records per turnover

article.headline: UT-Martin 86, Bethel (Tenn.) 83
article.story: MARTIN, Tenn. -- Myles Taylor scored 22 points and Tennessee-Martin outlasted Bethel (Tenn.), the NAIA's top scoring team, 86-83 Tuesday night after 30 lead changes. The Skyhawks (3-9), who snapped a four-game skid, trailed by eight with 1:57 left in the first half and 48-46 at the break. The Wildcats built a 58-49 cushion with 15:41 to go. After Tennessee-Martin tied it at 64, the game was knotted on four more occasions, including 80-80 with 3:06 left. The lead again went back and forth. Mike Liabo hit two baskets for the Skyhawks and Bethel's Erin Harris made a free throw and a layup. Omari Minor then went 1 of 2 on two trips to the foul line in the final 11 seconds. Tennessee-Martin won the schools' previous 11 meetings by an average of 29.9 points. Jarvis Palmer had 25 points for the Wildcats (9-4), who came in averaging 88 points.
